de.mrapp.android.adapter.expandablelist

Class AbstractExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType,DecoratorType extends AbstractExpandableListDecorator<GroupType,ChildType>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.support.v7.widget.RecyclerView.Adapter<de.mrapp.android.util.view.ViewHolder>
      • de.mrapp.android.adapter.expandablelist.AbstractExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType,DecoratorType>
  • Type Parameters:
    GroupType - The type of the underlying data of the adapter's group items
    ChildType - The type of the underlying data of the adapter's child items
    DecoratorType - The type of the decorator, which allows to customize the appearance of the views, which are used to visualize the group and child items of the adapter
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.widget.ExpandableListAdapter, android.widget.HeterogeneousExpandableList, Adapter<android.widget.ExpandableListView>, DataStructure, Parameterizable, Restorable, ExpandableGridViewAdapter, EnableStateExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>, FilterableExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>, ItemStateExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>, SortableExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>, ExpandableRecyclerViewAdapter, Loggable, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractEnableStateExpandableListAdapter

    public abstract class AbstractExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType,DecoratorType extends AbstractExpandableListDecorator<GroupType,ChildType>>
extends android.support.v7.widget.RecyclerView.Adapter<de.mrapp.android.util.view.ViewHolder>
implements ExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>
    An abstract base class for all adapters, whose underlying data is managed as a list of arbitrary group and child items. Such an adapter's purpose is to provide the underlying data for visualization using a ExpandableListView widget.
    Since:
    0.1.0
